  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 490 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Halve @Green Bell Pepper{2} lengthwise; remove stems and seeds. Place
on a #baking sheet{} and drizzle each half with @Vegetable Oil{}; rub to coat.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until browned and softened,
~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add @Israeli Couscous{1/2%cup} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring,
until toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add 3/4 cup water. Bring to a boil, then cover
and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Keep
covered off heat. While couscous cooks, halve, peel, and dice @Yellow Onion{1}.
Finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably ovenproof, #pan{} over medium heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add
@Ground Beef{10%ounce} and @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}; season with salt
and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked
through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir @Tomato Paste{1.5%ounce} and diced tomato into pan with beef mixture until
thoroughly combined. Add @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and 1/3 cup water; season
with salt and pepper. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in
couscous until thoroughly combined. Turn off heat.

Once bell peppers are done, remove from oven and stuff each half with as much
filling as will fit. Place in pan with remaining filling, nestling each stuffed
pepper half into the mixture.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture to a small baking dish and
> arrange stuffed pepper halves in there.

Sprinkle evenly with @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup}.

Bake stuffed peppers on middle rack until cheese has melted, ~{3-4%minutes}.
Divide remaining filling between plates. Top with stuffed peppers and serve.